{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-27T18:30:25.824Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777314625823_0","parameters":{"content":"# T-018: Wire generation status into operator_diagnostics.py\n\n## Problem Statement\nThe face/inkplate display needs to show the current generation status (e.g., \"♫ generating\" or \"♫ queued: N\"). This information is written to `/tmp/generation_status.json` but is not currently read or exposed by `operator_diagnostics.py`.\n\n## Technical Approach\n1. Add a new function `generation_status(path: Path | None = None) -> dict[str, object]` to `my-claw/tools/senseweave/operator_diagnostics.py`.\n2. The function will read `/tmp/generation_status.json` (or the provided path).\n3. Handle missing/stale/corrupt files gracefully, defaulting to 0 queue depth and not generating.\n4. Extract `queue_depth` as an integer.\n5. Add a `caption` field to the returned dictionary:\n   - \"♫ queued: {N}\" if `queue_depth > 1`\n   - \"♫ generating\" if `queue_depth == 1` or `is_generating` is True\n   - \"♫ ready\" otherwise\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- `operator_diagnostics.py::generation_status() -> dict` reads `/tmp/generation_status.json`\n  - VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py -k test_generation_status_reads_file`\n- Returns sanitized dict suitable for face/inkplate rendering\n  - VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py -k test_generation_status_returns_dict`\n- Adds a one-line caption: \"♫ generating\" when queue depth > 0, \"♫ ready\" otherwise\n  - VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py -k test_generation_status_captions`\n- Tests assert reader handles missing/stale/corrupt status file\n  - VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py -k test_generation_status_handles_errors`","file_path":"/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw/specs/t-018@20260427t001208z-spec.md"}}
